 227:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to initialize the USART
 228:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     in synchronous SPI master/slave mode.
 229:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****       (+) For the synchronous SPI mode only these parameters can be configured:
 230:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) Baud Rate
 231:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) Word Length
 232:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) Stop Bit
 233:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) Parity: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 234:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****              in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 235:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) USART polarity
 236:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) USART phase
 237:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) USART LastBit
 238:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) Receiver/transmitter modes
